begin_memory_text: We talked about where we lived, and found that we were in a similar location, so we talked about what it is like to live here.
middle_memory_text: We talked about our kids and how virtual learning is going, and what virtual school is like for everyone.
end_memory_text: What we plan to do for the holidays, and how different people are responding to the pandemic in different ways.
rest_of_day_open: I see it going okay. We're almost to the end! Today we have to finish school and my daughter has a project. Tonight I have to pick up a few things, including an ottoman from Ikea, which I am greatly looking forward to because I am pregnant and it will feel wonderful to put my feet up while I sit! I'm looking forward to the weekend because my husband will be home from work.
critical_positive: We both exhibited interest and curiosity about the other person, which meant we both asked and answered questions to learn more about each other and keep the conversation going. The flow of the conversation was very natural, and we found several things in common. We also commiserated about how hard things are right now.
critical_negative: I wouldn't say there was anything that didn't work. We had a very slightly slow start, and then ending the conversation was slightly awkward, but that was more because I mentioned the time was up and we were good to go, which actually wasn't a natural end point to the conversation. Other than that there was nothing that didn't work.

begin_memory_text: We talked about where we live and what we do for work. We also talked about her kids. They are nine and eleven, and she is expecting a boy.
middle_memory_text: We talked about the pandemic. She was furloughed in March and laid off in July. She worked in the restaurant industry. Her husband is an executive chef and is still working.
end_memory_text: We talked about what we will do for the holidays. We also talked about her mom coming out when her baby is born. We talked about where we went to college.
rest_of_day_open: I see my week going well. I will continue to homeschool my son and teach my classes. I will clean my house and deliver for DoorDash this weekend, which will help me make some extra money. My son and I will get to spend time with my mom this weekend, which will be nice.
critical_positive: We had some things in common. We both have kids, so we were able to discuss that. We also both live in California, so we were able to talk about that as well. She was familiar with the city where I live and where I went to school. My brother-in-law works in the same industry that she does, so we could also talk about that.
critical_negative: I did not feel very comfortable talking with my partner. She didn't smile very much, so I am not sure if she liked me. I also felt like there were way too many gaps. I am not very good at having conversations, so my awkwardness probably made her feel uncomfortable.
